ProtoTheorem:
. "Let $n$ be an integer that is a product of distinct primes 
   and let $d,e\in\mathbf{N}$ be such that $p-1\mid de-1$ for 
   each prime $p\mid n$. Then $a^{de} \equiv a\pmod{n}$ for all
   $a\in\mathbf{Z}$."
